data.event: Once a busy port on the Mississippi River, Princeton today is covered by forest and a portion of the Mississippi Levee.
In 1830, Princeton became Washington County's second county seat after the first county seat, New Mexico, caved into the Mississippi River.

event.title: incorporated the "Lake Washington and Deer Creek Railroad and Banking Company" in 1836

data.event: The Mississippi Legislature incorporated the "Lake Washington and Deer Creek Railroad and Banking Company" in 1836.
Only a portion of the railroad bed was completed before the company's charter was repealed in 1839.
